requestBody.description:
Information about a person merged from various data sources such as the
authenticated user's contacts and profile data.

Most fields can have multiple items. The items in a field have no guaranteed
order, but each non-empty field is guaranteed to have exactly one field with
`metadata.primary` set to true.

items.description:
A person's physical address. May be a P.O. box or street address. All fields
are optional.

countryCode.description:
The [ISO 3166-1 alpha-2](http://www.iso.org/iso/country_codes.htm) country
code of the address.

extendedAddress.description: The extended address of the address; for example, the apartment number.

formattedType.description:
The read-only type of the address translated and formatted in the viewer's
account locale or the `Accept-Language` HTTP header locale.

formattedValue.description:
The unstructured value of the address. If this is not set by the user it
will be automatically constructed from structured values.

primary.description:
True if the field is the primary field; false if the field is a secondary
field.

etag.description:
**Only populated in `person.metadata.sources`.**

The [HTTP entity tag](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP_ETag) of the
source. Used for web cache validation.

verified field is typically a name, email address, phone number, or

poBox.description: The P.O. box of the address.

postalCode.description: The postal code of the address.

region.description: The region of the address; for example, the state or province.

type.description:

values:

* `home`
* `work`
* `other`

Metadata about a source of type PROFILE.

updateTime.description:
**Only populated in `person.metadata.sources`.**

Last update timestamp of this source.

verified.description:
True if the field is verified; false if the field is unverified. A
verified field is typically a name, email address, phone number, or
website that has been confirmed to be owned by the person.

value.description:
The relationship status. The value can be custom or one of these
predefined values:

* `single`
* `inARelationship`
* `engaged`
* `married`
* `itsComplicated`
* `openRelationship`
* `widowed`
* `inDomesticPartnership`
* `inCivilUnion`

items.description: A person's past or current residence.

current.description:
True if the residence is the person's current residence;
false if the residence is a past residence.

primary.description:
True if the field is the primary field; false if the field is a secondary
field.

etag.description:

source. Used for web cache validation.
